⊕meta⊕
name = "find-unused-sky-workflows"
description = "Cross-reference every .sky in a dir against skyway run history; list never-run / long-stale files as advisory deletion candidates. Prints ready-to-paste delete commands but deletes nothing."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※list※
Enumerate all .sky files in $SKY_DIR (no filtering, no prior state; reads dir passed via --var).
※※

§list§
bash_file = "./scripts/list.sh"
§§

※runs※
Capture `skyway logs` output; depends_on = ["list"], trigger_rule = all_done (default). Runs after list completes; receives $SKY_OUTPUT_LIST.
※※

§runs§
depends_on = ["list"]
bash_file = "./scripts/runs.sh"
§§

※report※
Cross-reference each file against run history (SEEN-IN-LOGS vs NEVER); depends_on = ["list", "runs"], trigger_rule = all_done (default). Reads $SKY_OUTPUT_LIST and $SKY_OUTPUT_RUNS; prints deletion suggestions.
※※

§report§
depends_on = ["list", "runs"]
bash_file = "./scripts/report.sh"
§§

※※
find-unused-sky-workflows — advisory dead-workflow scanner (pure bash, no Claude, no cost)

WHAT IT DOES
  Lists every <name>.sky in --var dir, cross-references each basename against
  the output of `skyway logs`, and classifies it:
    SEEN-IN-LOGS  name appears (case-insensitively) somewhere in run history
    NEVER         name does NOT appear in run history -> deletion CANDIDATE
  For every NEVER file it prints a ready-to-paste command line:
    skyway run delete-sky-workflow --var dir="<dir>" --var name=<name>
  It deletes NOTHING. Always exits 0 — this is discovery, not enforcement.

HONESTY / CAVEATS (read before acting on output)
  - "NEVER" is ADVISORY. It only means the name was not found in `skyway logs`.
  - It is wrong if log retention has aged the run out, or if the workflow's
    `name = "..."` in ⊕meta⊕ differs from its filename (matching is by
    filename basename appearing in the log text).
  - `skyway logs` output format is not a stable contract; this scan greps the raw
    text case-insensitively and tolerates an empty/unavailable log (then every
    file reports NEVER). Verify before deleting anything.
  - Recently-created-but-never-run files will also show NEVER. That is correct
    but may be intentional. Human judgment required.

DAG
  list ──► runs ──► report
   │                 ▲
   └─────────────────┘
  list   bash: print basename of each "$SKY_DIR"/*.sky (one per line); errors if dir empty/missing
  runs   bash: capture `skyway logs` into a /tmp mktemp file, print it, rm the file; never fails the run
  report bash: for each file mark SEEN-IN-LOGS / NEVER; print delete suggestions; exit 0 always

RUN
  skyway run find-unused-sky-workflows --var dir=/abs/path/to/.sky/workflows

VARS
  dir   (required)  Absolute path to a directory containing .sky files. -> $SKY_DIR
※※
